<!-- Node: "Half-life 2 - coming soon?" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Half-life 2 - coming soon?</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/3" title="View user profile.">Tycho</a> on Thursday, September 16, 2004 - 13:28</small><br /><br />
On the <a href="http://www.hl2fallout.com/">Half-life 2 Fallout forums</a>, Gabe Newell has, with very few words, announced that VALVe has just sent the first Half-life 2 release candidate to <i>Vivendi Universal Games</i>, in <a href="http://www.hl2fallout.com/forums/index.php?showtopic=6610&st=0">this thread</a>.<br />
<br />
As you probably know, there has been two cases where unauthorized users have posted fake announcements about the status of HL2, in the name of Gabe Newell, but this time, staff from Half-life 2 fallout have confirmed that this thread was actually made from a VALVe IP.<br />
<br />
Although
<br /><br />
<a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/616#comment" title="Jump to the first comment of this posting.">4 comments</a> &middot; <a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/616" title="Read the rest of this posting." class="read-more"><b>Read more</b></a> &middot; 98 reads
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "Action Unreal Tournament Beta 0" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Action Unreal Tournament Beta 0</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/120" title="View user profile.">KaMiKrAe-Z</a> on Wednesday, September 15, 2004 - 01:10</small><br /><br />
The Action Unreal Tournament (AUT) mod, created for Unreal Tournament 2003/2004, was released only a few days ago. AUT is the sequal to Action Quake2 (AQ2) and Action Half-Life (AHL), both popular mods in their own rights. While the team that created AUT has only one orignal member of the A-Team that brought out AQ2, the aim of the mod remains the same: to re-create the feel of your favourite action movie, without having to pay for a ticket!
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/login" >Login</a> or <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/register" >Register</a> to post comments &middot; <a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/615" title="Read the rest of this posting." class="read-more"><b>Read more</b></a> &middot; 62 reads
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "Hostile Intent v.1.3.5. Release" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Hostile Intent v.1.3.5. Release</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2203" title="View user profile.">pepper</a> on Tuesday, September 14, 2004 - 10:06</small><br /><br />
<p>The Half-Life Mod:<br>
Hostile-Intent has released there latest version: v.1.3.5.<br>
You will find more information at the <a href="http://www.hostileintent.org">Hostile-Intent</a> Website.<br><br>
They have many new interesting features like bullet penetration and new walking animations.</p>
This mod also features the ironsight system, which means you have no crosshair to aim but you have to raise your weapon to aim and fire, And it requires a lot of teamwork and strategy.<br><br>
This is in no way a counter-strike rip-off.<br>
So go check it out right now!!
<br /><br />
